==Mandarin==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ltc|cmn}} {{IPAchar|/ʃɣiɪ/}}, from {{etyl|och|cmn}} {{IPAchar|/*srij/}}, likely from {{etyl|pal|cmn}} {{term|𐭱𐭩𐭥|tr=šēr|lang=pal|sc=Phli}}.

{{Hani|獅 / 獅子 / 師 / 師子}} was first mentioned in the ''{{w|Book of Han}}'' (finished 111 CE), in the description of the "specialties" of the {{Hani|[[烏弋山離]]}} country in the {{w|Western Regions}}.  {{Hani|烏弋山離}} in {{etyl|och|-}} had a pronunciation of {{IPAchar|/*ʔa lək sren raj/}}, hence referring to *''Alexandria'', likely "{{w|Alexandria Prophthasia}}", which was part of the {{w|Parthian Empire}} during the time of Han, speaking an Indo-Iranian language.

